can we used .keep=TRUE
Short answer: no, not with semi_join().

Why?

.keep_all = TRUE (or .keep = TRUE in some contexts) is not an argument for semi_join().

semi_join() only returns rows from the left table (bookings)
It never brings columns from rooms
So there’s nothing extra to “keep”
