🍋 ROOM & BOOKING JOIN SCENARIOS CHEAT SHEET (dplyr + join_by)

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 BASIC OVERLAP
------------------------------------------------------------

1) Bookings that overlap with room availability

LOGIC:
booking_start <= availability_end
AND
booking_end >= availability_start

INTERPRETATION:
Any intersection between two time ranges

------------------------------------------------------------

2) Rooms that have at least one booking overlap

LOGIC:
Same overlap condition, but grouped by room_id

TIP:
Use inner_join + filter OR semi_join on bookings

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 NO MATCH CASES
------------------------------------------------------------

3) Bookings that do NOT match any room availability

LOGIC:
anti_join(bookings, rooms, by = "room_id")

INTERPRETATION:
No relationship at all

------------------------------------------------------------

4) Rooms never booked

LOGIC:
anti_join(rooms, bookings, by = "room_id")

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 FULL vs PARTIAL OVERLAP
------------------------------------------------------------

5) Booking fully inside availability

LOGIC:
availability_start <= booking_start
AND
booking_end <= availability_end

INTERPRETATION:
Booking is completely contained inside window

------------------------------------------------------------

6) Booking partially overlaps availability

CASE A: starts before, ends inside
booking_start < availability_start
AND booking_end inside window

CASE B: starts inside, ends after
booking_start inside window
AND booking_end > availability_end

INTERPRETATION:
One boundary outside, one inside

------------------------------------------------------------

7) Booking extends beyond availability

LOGIC:
booking_start < availability_start
AND booking_end > availability_end

INTERPRETATION:
Booking fully covers availability window

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 CONFLICT DETECTION
------------------------------------------------------------

8) Double booking (overlapping bookings same room)

LOGIC:
start1 <= end2
AND end1 >= start2
AND same room_id

INTERPRETATION:
Two bookings collide in time

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 TIME-BASED WINDOW CHECKS
------------------------------------------------------------

9) Booking start inside availability

LOGIC:
availability_start <= booking_start <= availability_end

INTERPRETATION:
Only START is checked

------------------------------------------------------------

10) Booking end inside availability

LOGIC:
availability_start <= booking_end <= availability_end

INTERPRETATION:
Only END is checked

------------------------------------------------------------

11) Booking starts before availability but ends inside

LOGIC:
booking_start < availability_start
AND booking_end inside window

INTERPRETATION:
Late fitting booking

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 GAP ANALYSIS
------------------------------------------------------------

12) Bookings not fitting any availability

LOGIC:
anti_join OR NOT EXISTS match

INTERPRETATION:
No valid window for booking

------------------------------------------------------------

13) Gaps between bookings

LOGIC IDEA:
order by date per room → lag() / lead()

INTERPRETATION:
Time between bookings

------------------------------------------------------------

14) Unused availability periods

LOGIC:
availability rows with no booking overlap

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 NEAREST MATCHING
------------------------------------------------------------

15) Closest availability to booking

LOGIC IDEA:
compute distance between dates:
abs(booking_start - availability_start)

INTERPRETATION:
Not exact match, but nearest time window

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 MULTI-MATCH
------------------------------------------------------------

16) Bookings matching multiple availability windows

LOGIC:
join_by only (no filtering collapse)

INTERPRETATION:
One booking → multiple valid windows

------------------------------------------------------------

🔵 FILTERING LOGIC RULE (VERY IMPORTANT)

WHENEVER YOU SEE:
"within window", "inside range"
→ use BETWEEN logic:
start <= value <= end

WHENEVER YOU SEE:
"overlap"
→ use:
start1 <= end2 AND end1 >= start2

WHENEVER YOU SEE:
"before / after"
→ use strict inequalities (< or >)

------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 FINAL INTERPRETATION RULE

Think every question as:

1) WHAT VALUE AM I CHECKING?
   - start_date OR end_date

2) WHAT RELATIONSHIP?
   - inside window
   - overlap
   - outside window

3) WHICH SIDE?
   - booking vs availability vs booking vs booking
