*******************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
🍋 ROOM & BOOKING JOIN SCENARIOS MASTER CHEAT SHEET (ALL POSSIBILITIES)

This sheet is about HOW TO THINK, not just memorising cases.

------------------------------------------------------------
🔴 1. CORE TIME RELATIONSHIP TYPES (MOST IMPORTANT)
------------------------------------------------------------

Every question is one of these 4 patterns:

A) INSIDE (contained)
booking is fully inside window

availability_start <= booking_start
AND booking_end <= availability_end

------------------------------------------------------------

B) OVERLAP (any intersection)
any part touches

booking_start <= availability_end
AND booking_end >= availability_start

------------------------------------------------------------

C) OUTSIDE (no overlap)
completely separate

booking_end < availability_start
OR booking_start > availability_end

------------------------------------------------------------

D) PARTIAL OVERLAP (boundary crossing)
mix of inside + outside

CASE 1: starts before, ends inside
booking_start < availability_start
AND booking_end BETWEEN window

CASE 2: starts inside, ends after
booking_start BETWEEN window
AND booking_end > availability_end

CASE 3: covers whole window
booking_start < availability_start
AND booking_end > availability_end

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 2. SINGLE POINT CHECKS (VERY COMMON)
------------------------------------------------------------

A) START ONLY INSIDE WINDOW
availability_start <= booking_start <= availability_end

B) END ONLY INSIDE WINDOW
availability_start <= booking_end <= availability_end

C) START BEFORE WINDOW
booking_start < availability_start

D) END AFTER WINDOW
booking_end > availability_end

------------------------------------------------------------
🟡 3. BOOKING vs BOOKING (CONFLICTS)
------------------------------------------------------------

A) DOUBLE BOOKING (same room)
start1 <= end2 AND end1 >= start2

B) EXACT SAME BOOKING
start1 = start2 AND end1 = end2

C) BACK-TO-BACK (no overlap)
end1 = start2 OR end1 < start2

D) GAP BETWEEN BOOKINGS
end1 < start2

------------------------------------------------------------
🟢 4. ROOM vs BOOKING LOGIC TYPES
------------------------------------------------------------

A) VALID BOOKING
inside availability window

B) INVALID BOOKING (outside all windows)
no match found (anti_join)

C) MULTI-MATCH BOOKING
one booking fits multiple availability windows

D) PARTIAL FIT
booking overlaps but not fully contained

------------------------------------------------------------
🔵 5. JOIN STRATEGY GUIDE (dplyr THINKING)
------------------------------------------------------------

INNER_JOIN:
→ find actual matches + combine data

LEFT_JOIN:
→ keep all bookings, add room info

SEMI_JOIN:
→ filter bookings (no extra columns)

ANTI_JOIN:
→ find missing/unmatched rows

------------------------------------------------------------
🔴 6. HOW TO TRANSLATE ANY QUESTION (IMPORTANT)
------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1: Identify OBJECTS
- booking vs room
- booking vs booking

STEP 2: Identify VALUE CHECKED
- start_date OR end_date OR both

STEP 3: Identify RELATION TYPE

WORDS → LOGIC

"inside / within" → BETWEEN
"overlap" → interval overlap formula
"before" → <
"after" → >
"touching" → <= or >=
"no match" → anti_join
"conflict" → overlap

------------------------------------------------------------
🟣 7. UNIVERSAL FORMULAS (MEMORISE THESE ONLY)
------------------------------------------------------------

INSIDE:
A_start <= B_start AND B_end <= A_end

OVERLAP:
A_start <= B_end AND A_end >= B_start

NO OVERLAP:
A_end < B_start OR A_start > B_end

START INSIDE:
A_start <= B_start <= A_end

END INSIDE:
A_start <= B_end <= A_end

------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 8. FINAL THINKING MODEL

Every question =

1) WHICH ENTITY?
   booking? room? booking vs booking?

2) WHICH COLUMN?
   start or end or both?

3) WHICH RELATION?
   inside / overlap / outside / conflict?

4) WHICH TOOL?
   semi_join / inner_join / anti_join + filter

------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 KEY TRUTH

There are ONLY 3 real patterns:
- INSIDE
- OVERLAP
- OUTSIDE

Everything else is variation of these.

